# Pre-push CI gates and commit attribution

Before committing or pushing, run the same checks as `.github/workflows/ci.yml`. Failed CI wastes GitHub compute. See root `AGENTS.md`.

Rust changes (`src-tauri/`, `crates/`, Cargo files):

```bash
cargo fmt --all -- --check
cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings
cargo test --workspace
```

Frontend changes (`src/`, etc.):

```bash
pnpm build
pnpm test
```

`cargo check` alone is not sufficient. Fix fmt/clippy locally; do not weaken CI.

## Never credit Cursor as co-author

After any agent `git commit`, check `git log -1 --format=%B`. If you see `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>`, strip it before pushing:

```bash
git log -1 --format=%B | sed '/Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>/d;/^---------$/d' | git commit --amend -F -
```

Do not add Co-authored-by trailers for Cursor or similar tools. Commits must be authored only as the human repo owner.
